The Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Baba, has acquired 55 additional Lorries, 5 water tankers, 2 coaster buses and 15 Armoured Personnel Carriers (APCs) to fight insecurity across the country. This was revealed by Muyiwa Adejobi, the Force Public Relations Officer (FPRO), on Sunday via his Twitter page in a statement titled ‘TACTICAL OPERATIONS: IGP PROCURES  ADDITIONAL ASSETS  FOR STRATEGIC DEPLOYMENT, AGGRESSIVE PATROLS’. Adejobi wrote, “In a bid to restrategise for better security networking in Nigeria, the Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Baba psc(+), NPM, fdc has acquired  55 additional Lorries, 5 water tankers, 2 coaster buses and 15 Armoured Personnel Carriers (APCs). “To aid strategic deployment of tactical squads to tackle Insecurity across the length and breadth of the country, especially in the crisis affected areas.” TACTICAL OPERATIONS: IGP PROCURES  ADDITIONAL ASSETS  FOR STRATEGIC DEPLOYMENT, AGGRESSIVE PATROLS*As IGP Steps Up Police ICT Platforms* In a bid to restrategise for better security networking in Nigeria, the Inspector-General of Police, IGP Usman Alkali Baba psc(+), NPM, fdc,